smb is a chatroom for multi user systems
chatrooms are spawned with ./smb -C and can contain arbitrarily many rooms

usage:
      ./smb -C [board_name] - creates a board with name [board_name]
      ./smb    [board_path] - joins board at path [board_path]

client commands:

      [message]:
            sends message to current room

      /[h]elp:
            prints this information

      /[j]oin  [room_name]:
      /[r]room [room_name]:
            join room with room_name

      /[n]ext:
            switch to next room with same first char as current

      /[c]reate [room_name]:
            creates a room with name room_name

      /[l]ist:
            lists all rooms, current room will be blue

      /[w]hich:
            prints current room name and reference number

      /[e]xit:
      /e[x]it:
            exits current room
